A vile maggot from Dark Souls. Straight & posed models. Made for miniature tabletop games. Models are without base.

This model is based off of its appearance Dark Souls series:

I made these models myself - they are hand sculpted from basic cylinder shape in blender software.
- No custom brushes or library of tricks. yet.
- You can scale the model however you want.
- The models may be small, they are still chunky enough to be easily printed on low-end FDM machines without causing clogging issues (supports & brim required).
- You can use glossy finish to make it look more yucky.

(photos & tutorial will be uploaded later)

If you have any suggestions, let me know. I can do similar models if you provide screenshots.
Be creative :)

Hello this is my first proper upload of anything here!

Been needing Epic Scale Plaguereapers from the Chaos God of Decay for a while, and after converting a few, I got into 3D printing, so this was my first major project. I did use a lot of parts from other builds, so there's a list at the bottom for that. I certainly did not build these things from scratch, I just stuck things together and mutated them, so I can take no credit for the finished designs.

Not all of these are perfect, like I say this is my first real go at designing things. Some will be better printed out as resin, and some in finer detail than what I could manage on my humble Monoprice printer. But they should certainly do the trick on the battlefield.

You'll see some of these have the main cannons attached as one piece, where there are separate cannons to chose from for others. Please feel free to fiddle and adjust these how you see fit.

The main hull is remixed slightly from this:
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3766158

The remaining bits and pieces come from the following links. Many thanks to those folks for designing and allowing free reign on these creations:
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3737334
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4012912
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2434231
